cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks such as object segmentation and pose estimation using RGBD data, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep neural network architectures, which is a common topic in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of the generated dataset for robotic manipulation tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. The use of human-assisted ICP-fitting of object meshes for labeling the 3D reconstruction suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the amount and quality of training data required for high performance from a DNN architecture, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
